HEADWORD: Retinoic acid
<hw>Ret`in*o"ic ac"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A retinoid compound (<chform>C20H28O2</chform>),
closely related to vitamin A. It is also called
<altname>tretinoin</altname> and <altname>vitamin A
acid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
